 Finally, it complements our knowledge of the philosophy of two major Aristotelians, Herminos and his pupil, the great Alexander of Aphrodisias. This study is of immediate relevance to readers with an interest in philosophy, logic, history, and/or Greco-Roman antiquity. Because it concerns the use and abuse of fallacies, and ways to counteract them, it also has countless practical applications in all fields of mundane life.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aDialektik. 4aFehlschlüsse. 4aLogik. 4aPhilosophie.  adialectic.  afallacies.  alogic.  aphilosophy.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2024 Part 1z97831113321920 cEPUBz97831113330210 cprintz978311133266640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311133296340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783111332963423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783111332963/original  a978-3-11-133219-2  DG Plus DeG Package 2024 Part 1b2024  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_CL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles